e1"/> | |- |2007 |[[Timothy O'Sullivan (classicist)|Timothy O'Sullivan]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Breichner|first1=William M.|title=The Gildersleeve Prize for the Best Article Published in the American Journal of Philology in 2007 Has Been Presented to Timothy M. O'Sullivan|url=https://philpapers.org/rec/BRETGP-3|website=American Journal of Philology|pages=iii–iii|date=2008}}</ref> | |- |2008 |[[Judith Fletcher]] |A Trickster's Oath in the ''Homeric Hymn to Hermes''<ref>{{cite web|last1=Breichner|first1=William M.|title=The Gildersleeve Prize Winner for 2008|url=https://muse.jhu.edu/article/317362|website=American Journal of Philology|pages=iii–iii|doi=10.1353/ajp.0.0072|date=19 September 2009}}</ref> |- |2009 |[[Randy Pogorzelski]] |The Reassurance of Fratricide in the Aeneid<ref>{{cite web|title=Comparative Literature, Winter 2011|url=http://www.complit.ucsb.edu/sites/comparative-literature/files/CompLitNewsletter_W2011.pdf|publisher=University of Santa Barbara|accessdate=15 September 2017}}</ref> |- |2010 |[[Michael Squire]] |Making Myron's Cow Moo? Ecphrastic Epigram and the Poetics of Simulation<ref>{{cite web|title=The Gildersleeve Prize Winner for 2010|url=https://muse.jhu.edu/article/451834|website=American Journal of Philology|pages=iii–iii|doi=10.1353/ajp.2011.0025|date=29 September 2011}}</ref> |- |2011 | | |- |2012 |[[Rachel Ahern Knudsen]] |Poetic Speakers, Sophistic Words<ref>{{cite web|last1=Breichner|first1=William M.|title=The Gildersleeve Prize for the Best Article Published in the American Journal of Philology in 2012 has been Presented to Rachel Ahern Knudsen, University of Oklahoma|url=https://muse.jhu.edu/article/521625|website=American Journal of Philology|pages=iii–iii|doi=10.1353/ajp.2013.0029|date=18 September 2013}}</ref> |- |2013 |[[James E. G. Zetzel]] |A Contract on Ameria: Law and Legality in Cicero's ''Pro Roscio Amerino''<ref>{{cite web|last1=Breichner|first1=William M.|title=The Gildersleeve Prize for the Best Article Published in the A