[[File:Norvegia phonetic alphabet.svg|thumb]] '''Norvegia''' ([[Latin]] for ''[[Norway]]'') is a [[phonetic]] [[transcription (linguistics)|transcription]] system which was developed by Norwegian [[linguist]] [[Johan Storm]] in 1884. Norvegia is still employed in the teaching of [[Scandinavian studies]] at Norwegian universities.
